the nice part about the `suspense:boolean` api was that you could do this:

```
const [articleResult] = useQueries({
  queries: [
    { queryKey: ['article', id], queryFn: getArticleById, suspense: true },
    // Prefetch
    { queryKey: ['article-comments', id], queryFn: getArticleCommentsById, suspense: false },
  ],
})
```

and it would work as expected: Both queries start at the same time, but you'd only wait for the suspense: true query to finish before rendering the component ...
